[[File:College des Freres Jaffa.jpg|thumb|'''College des Freres Jaffa''']]
'''Collège des Frères de Jaffa''' is a French international school in the [[Jaffa]] area of [[Tel Aviv]]. A part of the [[La Sallian educational institutions]], it opened in 1882.<ref name=Amba>"[http://www.ambafrance-il.org/College-des-Freres-de-Jaffa,4813 Collège des Frères de Jaffa]." [[Embassy of France in Israel]]. Retrieved on September 17, 2015.</ref> Originally it was in the [[Mutasarrifate of Jerusalem]], [[Ottoman Empire]], before being in the [[Mandatory Palestine|British Mandate of Palestine]]; currently it is in Israel.

Hosting one of six French international high school programmes in Israel, it serves levels ''maternelle'' (preschool) through ''terminale'' (final year of high school),<ref name=Amba/> with ''quatrième'' through ''terminale'' under the [[AEFE]].<ref>"[http://www.aefe.fr/reseau-scolaire-mondial/rechercher-un-etablissement/israel-jaffa-college-des-freres Collège des Frères]." [[AEFE]]. Retrieved on 17 September 2015.</ref>

