'''''Marilyn Anne''''' is a three-masted auxiliary [[schooner]] that was built in 1919 as '''''Frem''''' by her Danish owner. She was sold to Sweden in 1938 and later renamed '''''Vestvåg'''''. In 1958, she was sold to Denmark and renamed '''''Vest'''''. Following her sale to an American owner in 1968, she was renamed ''Marilyn Anne''. In 1977, she became a training ship for disadvantaged Danish children.
==Description== As built, the ship was {{convert|92|ft|7|in|m|2|order=flip}} long, with a beam of {{convert|24|ft|7|in|m|2|order=flip}}, a depth of {{convert|9|ft|5|in|m|2|order=flip}},<ref name=Frem30/> and a draught of {{convert|8|ft|6|in|m|2|abbr=on|order=flip}}.<ref name=Oktett>{{cite web |url=http://sailing-ships.oktett.net/648.html |title=Frem |publisher=Fredrik Sandström |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref> She was assessed at {{GRT|136}}, {{NRT|119}}.<ref name=Frem30>{{cite journal |url=http://www.plimsollshipdata.org/pdffile.php?name=30a0100.pdf |title=Lloyd's Register, Navires a Voiles |journal=Lloyd's List |author=Lloyd's of London |year=1930 |publisher=Plimsoll Ship Data |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref>
==History== ''Frem'' was built by Erik B. Kromann at [[Marstal]], Denmark and was initially operated by him. Her port of registry was Marstal and the [[Code Letters]] NWPH were allocated.<ref name=Frem30/> In 1932,<ref name=Frem34/> she was fitted with an auxiliary oil engine. She was reassessed as {{GRT|141}}, {{NRT|107}}.<ref name=Frem33>{{cite journal |url=http://www.plimsollshipdata.org/pdffile.php?name=33a0688.pdf |title=Lloyd's Register, Navires a Voiles |journal=Lloyd's List |author=Lloyd's of London |year=1933 |publisher=Plimsoll Ship Data |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref> This was a 2-cylinder Single Cycle Single Action [[diesel engine]], rated at 54[[nominal horsepower|nhp]]. It was made by A/S Tuxham, [[Copenhagen]]. In 1934, her Code Letters were changed to OUTB.<ref name=Frem34>{{cite journal |url=http://www.plimsollshipdata.org/pdffile.php?name=34a0221.pdf |title=Lloyd's Register, Navires a Vapeuer et a Moteurs de Moins de 300tx, Chalutiers &c |journal=Lloyd's List |author=Lloyd's of London |year=1934 |publisher=Plimsoll Ship Data |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref>
In 1939, ''Frem'' was sold to Janne Nielsen of [[Skårhamn]], Sweden. Her port of registry was changed to Skårhamn. The Code Letters SEFW were allocated.<ref name=Frem39>{{cite journal |url=http://www.plimsollshipdata.org/pdffile.php?name=39a0250.pdf |title=Lloyd's Register, Steamers & Motorships under 300 tons, Trawlers &c |journal=Lloyd's List |author=Lloyd's of London |year=1939 |publisher=Plimsoll Ship Data |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref> In 1940, she was renamed ''Vestvåg'' and her Code Letters were changed to SFBI.<ref name=Vestvag40>{{cite journal |url=http://www.plimsollshipdata.org/pdffile.php?name=40b0561.pdf |title=Lloyd's Register, Steamers & Motorships under 300 tons, Trawlers &c |journal=Lloyd's List |author=Lloyd's of London |year=1940 |publisher=Plimsoll Ship Data |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref>
In 1958, ''Vestvåg'' was sold to a Danish owner.<ref name=History>{{cite web |url=http://www.marilyn-anne.dk/historie/ |title=MARILYN ANNE's HISTORIE |language=Danish |publisher=Marilyn-Anne |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref> Her name was changed to ''Vest''. Her port of registry was [[Aalborg]] and the Code Letters OWLP were allocated.<ref name=Skibsregister58>{{cite journal |url=http://www.sbib.dk/documents/Skibslister/1958.pdf |title=Danmarks Skibsliste |year=1958 |publisher=Sjøfartens Bibliotek |author=Handelsministeriet |page=127 |language=Danish |accessdate=8 April 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304052808/http://www.sbib.dk/documents/Skibslister/1958.pdf |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df= }}</ref> In 1968, ''Vest'' was sold to an American owner who changed her name to ''Marilyn Anne'' and set about restoring her. In 1977, he abandoned the project and she was sold to the [[Struer Municipality]] in 1978. Following completion of the restoration work, ownership of ''Marilyn Anne'' was transferred to a holding company owned by the [[Herning Municipality|Herning]], [[Holstebro Municipality|Holstebro]] and Struer Municipalities.<ref name=History/> On 17 June 1996, Denmark issued a [[postage stamp]] depicting ''Marilyn Anne''.<ref name=Stamp>{{cite web |url=http://colnect.com/en/stamps/stamp/43550-Gaff-rigged_schooner_Marilyn_Anne_1919-Sailships-Denmark |title=Gaff-rigged schooner "Marilyn Anne" (1919) |publisher=Colnect |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref> The ship now{{when|date=April 2017}} serves as a school ship for disadvantaged children.<ref name=History/>
