{{Infobox School |name = Yangon Adventist Seminary |native_name = ရန္ကုန္သမၼာက်မ္းစာေက်ာင္း |image = |motto = "Fear of God is the beginning of Knowledge" |established = 1975 |type = [[Private school|Private]], (Protestant) [[Adventism|Adventist]] university |staff = |principal = |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |profess = |city = |province = |country = Myanmar |former_names = |campus = |free_label = |free = |colors = |nickname = YAS |affiliation = [[Seventh-day Adventist Church]] |footnotes = |website = [http://www.yas.myanmaradventist.org/] |address = 34 Natmauk Lane(1),Bahan, Yangon 11201 |telephone = |logo = }} {{Seventh-day Adventism}}
The '''Yangon Adventist Seminary''' (YAS) is a [[Christian]] institution owned and operated by [[Seventh-day Adventist]] Church since 1975. It is opened to young people who want to study in Christian Atmosphere Non-Christian student who can make the agreement to follow the rules and regulations of the school may be accepted. YAS is accredited by the Accrediting Association of Seventh-day Adventist School, Colleges, and Universities(AAA), Maryland, USA.
YAS has a proud tradition of recognizing outstanding, student achievement in all areas and practices Positive Behavior Support. The programs listed below are the prime examples of this tradition.
*Academic Performance Award *Athletic Award
